-This page covers how to implement custom serializers for your types.
+This page covers the current Java custom serializer API.

-## Basic Custom Serializer
+## Constructor Inputs

-In some cases, you may want to implement a serializer for your type, especially for classes that customize serialization using JDK `writeObject/writeReplace/readObject/readResolve`, which is very inefficient.
+Custom serializers should not retain `Fory`.

-For example, if you don't want the following `Foo#writeObject` to be invoked, you can implement a custom serializer:
+- Use `Config` when the serializer only depends on immutable configuration and can be shared.
+- Use `TypeResolver` when the serializer needs type metadata, generics, or nested dynamic dispatch.
+- If a serializer retains `TypeResolver`, it is usually not shareable and should keep the default
+  `shareable() == false`.

-```java
